    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-22T18:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-22T18:30:00-05:00" n="316"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-22T18:30:00-05:00"
                            >January 22, 1952—6: 30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 793. Re Membership: Although <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> does not have text Sov Res on membership
                    introduced Comite I,<note n="1" xml:id="d316fn1">The Soviet Union submitted the
                        following draft resolution to the First Committee on January 21: <hi
                            rend="italic">“The General Assembly, Recommends</hi> that the Security
                        Council should reconsider the applications of Albania, the People’s Republic
                        of Mongolia, Bulgaria, Romania, Hungary, Finland, Italy, Portugal, Ireland,
                        Jordan, Austria, Ceylon and Nepal, and consider the application of Libya for
                        membership in the United Nations.” (Doc. A/C.1/703). For the official text,
                        which is incorporated into the proceedings of the First Committee for
                        January 21, see <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> (VI). <hi rend="italic"
                            >First Committee</hi>, p. 221.</note> we gather from <gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 1127<note n="2" xml:id="d316fn2">The
                        Delegation’s Daily Unclassified Telegram Summary, January 21, 1952, 11: 45
                        p. m. (320/1–2152).</note> that text only requests that <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> reconsider 13 of old applications plus Libya.
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> assumes <gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                        >USDel</gloss> will oppose and vote against this Res, pointing out for
                    example it excludes <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>.</p>
                <p>In membership debate <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> shld also state case
                    for separate consideration applications on merits each case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
